commitResults.messageTitle: did Level-4, added 3 subclasses for Task
cleaned up code and did more error handling

commitResults.messageBody:
As of now data is lost once the bot stops running and tasks are not saved and are unretrievable

Therefore by saving these task in a local file and then loading in the data when bot is run again, allows information that was previously entered to be retrieved.

commitResults.messageTitle: add date and time feature for task
commitResults.messageBody:
date and time should be added for tasks with deadline or event with start and end dates and times instead of just strings

made use of java capabilities and libraries to do this and also fixed some bugs with the saving of tasks even after chatbot is closed

Everything was being done in the Bro.java file, so created more classes to handle different things.

The Ui class that handles all the printing required.
Storage which handles saving tasks and then loading them back in when the bot is run again.
Parser which handles parsing of user inputs.
TaskList which handles adding, deleting, marking, unmarking of tasks
Created package called bro, and moved all the classes under that package except for Bro.java

Added tests to see if addEvent throws Exception is wrong input is given.
Added test to see if parseDate can successfully parseDate is correct input is given
Somes names in shadowJar were wrong and the mainClass was not set correctly
Added JavaDocs for most methods and tweaked code to follow coding standard
Allows users to find tasks that contain a specific keyword using find command followed by keyword e.g. find book
Added necessary files for GUI, but the code from older files remains unchanged

Finished GUI Setup, mainly by changing all the ui commands to return String instead of printing to the screen. Ensured that files are still saved to and loading in properly. Did some aesthetic changes and changes to javadocs

commitResults.messageTitle: Add assertions to validate key assumptions
commitResults.messageBody:
Added assert statements to document and validate critical assumptions:
  - Ensure that input strings for creation of tasks have the necessary information
  - Validate that the task number to mark, unmark or delete is one and above
  - Check that the task string to load in contains the data needed

These assertions will help catch potential bugs early by ensuring that the input values meet the expected criteria. If an assertion fails, an AssertionError will be thrown, making it easier to diagnose issues during development.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor code for better code quality and readability
commitResults.messageBody:
Removed large chunks of unused code in the Bro.java file as the chatbot has switched from CLI to GUI

Edited the message displayed by BroException, if exception is thrown, to look better in the GUI

Made some minor changes and removed unused methods in Ui.java

This refactor improves robustness and code quality, and enhances code maintainability for future development.
